definitions.definition: Any of various large, long-legged wading birds of the genus Platalea , in the ibis family Threskiornithidae , that have a large, flat, spatulate bill.
A species of fish, Polyodon spathula , native to the river basins of Mississippi , Ohio , and Missouri , or its extinct close relatives.
